{"type":"message","id":"06dd5411","parentId":"1bfdfdbd","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:02:06.719Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_UvnDxEnD27x1MFefktBg83ym|fc_0cf340f19e5786830069af354e23488192b629e11a4e432103","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-09\n\n## Memory recovery run\n- Confirmed system back up and responsive.\n- User requested full pull of files/workers/projects/memory and recovery up to outage.\n- Verified workspace inventory and discovered memory artifacts were present.\n- Confirmed no extra workers/sub-agents active; main session active.\n- Reconstructed outage context from session transcript tail:\n  - 2026-03-05 evening showed repeated API-limit failures (`You have hit your ChatGPT usage limit`).\n- Created/updated long-term memory file (`MEMORY.md`) with current stable state and key historical notes.\n\n## Current known memory files\n- `memory/tonight-state-summary.md`\n- `memory/full-history-dump.md`\n- `memory/2026-03-05.md`\n- `memory/2026-03-09.md`\n- `memory/recovered-timeline.md`\n- `memory/job-pipeline.md`\n- `memory/weekly-lessons.md`\n- `memory/automation-ideas.md`\n- `MEMORY.md`\n\n## Memory intelligence pack created\n- `runbooks/OPENCLAW_MASTER_RUNBOOK.md`\n- `runbooks/CHEATSHEET_COMMANDS.md`\n- Added operational files for job intelligence and automation planning.\n\n## Durable operating preference captured\n- User explicitly wants OpenClaw run in a \"most effective\" operating rhythm with simple daily/weekly execution.\n- Daily focus should prioritize job intelligence + company research + outreach drafting, then logging outcomes.\n- Weekly focus should prioritize backup verification and lessons-learned updates to prevent repeat failures.\n- Keep workflows grounded in the new runbooks/memory pack as system-of-record, not ad-hoc chat-only instructions.\n\n## 1:04 PM status checkpoint (jobs/agents/schedule)\n- User requested a full list of scheduled jobs, agents, and schedule status.\n- Confirmed active