{"type":"message","id":"a0f1e136","parentId":"f4757255","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:02:18.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have found a list of 15 top company targets from recent outputs to use for company enrichment. Here are 5 companies selected along with role/contact hypotheses and relevance notes:\n\n1. GrazeMate\n   - Role Hypothesis: Could target product managers or innovation leads due to uncertain company size.\n   - Contact Hypothesis: LinkedIn profiles for founders or heads of growth.\n   - Relevance: Food tech or agritech potential, likely startup phase due to unknown size.\n\n2. Origami Robotics\n   - Role Hypothesis: Engineering leads or robotics specialists likely key roles.\n   - Contact Hypothesis: Engineering management or CEO on LinkedIn.\n   - Relevance: Robotics company, highly relevant for AI, automation, and hardware innovation projects.\n\n3. Librar Labs\n   - Role Hypothesis: Could be research scientists or software engineers.\n   - Contact Hypothesis: CTO or lead researchers.\n   - Relevance: May be involved in AI/machine learning or digital library/data tech.\n\n4. Carrot Labs\n   - Role Hypothesis: Possibly AI product managers or data scientists.\n   - Contact Hypothesis: Founders or analytics leads.\n   - Relevance: AI-based lab or analytics firm; likely relevant for AI and data roles.\n\n5. Aurorin CAD\n   - Role Hypothesis: Product managers or CAD software engineers.\n   - Contact Hypothesis: Product owners or leads involved in CAD development.\n   - Relevance: CAD software company; potential in software engineering and design tech areas.\n\nI will compile these with rough hypotheses and relevance notes for further enrichment. Would you like me to continue with detailed research on these companies?","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_059458aa171e5d2d0069af3554e7a481a187ed2a7dfcd80700\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1-mini","usage":{"input":520,"output":334,"cac